docs.title: Watkins Mill Computer Science Class of 2026 and 2027
docs.text: Before we get you publishing to this website, let's have a quick demo of how I use Gemini every day to help me publish to the web.

docs.title: Question 1: The Debate "Junior Developer"
docs.text: I use AI to write my Markdown formatting because I already know how to write it, and I just want to save time. What are some risks if you use AI to write code you don't understand?

docs.title: Question 2: The Test "Voice"
docs.text: If I use Gemini to polish my writing, is it still my writing? If I send an email that AI rewrote, am I lying to the person receiving it about how good a writer I am?

docs.title: Question 3: The "Brain" Test
docs.text: If i ask AI to create an image of Canada what would it do? I tried it and it showed me an flag of Canada with mapel syrup and small image Toronto city. But the thing is it did't ask me what type of image i wanted to create. This test was done in 2024 by the way.

docs.title: Ellias comment
docs.text: Personally I don't like Generative AI, I don't think the eviromental cost is worth what its does.
